node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Hannah | FTMH 💗 on July 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'You can post suicide prevention/ mental health hotlines all you want, but if you really want to help to prevent suicide, depression and self harm try being kinder to others online and in real life.'.

node.text:
What is the WORST thing someone has ever said to you regarding your mental health / illness? 

It takes two seconds to post a suicide hotline number. 2 seconds. Anyone can do that. But if you really want to make a difference to people’s mental health, be kind. 
You cannot post a quote online and then be horrible to people online/in real life. It’s important to be nice to everyone you meet, because you never truly know what somebody may be facing. ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Hannah | FTMH 💗 on July 12, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
I needed to post this tonight because I feel sad. I’m a human behind this account, not a robot. I have feelings and I feel things very hard. 

I’ve been checking my messages and seeing so many people telling me that I shouldn’t be open about my struggles & that I clearly don’t suffer from mental health if I can post online. All I ever want to do is show people they aren’t alone. And by me sharing my experiences and my journey (the good AND BAD!) that is what I’m hoping to do. It’s not easy to be so open to so many people, but I do it to help YOU GUYS.

This page was created by me to reduce the stigma of mental health, to show people it’s ok to speak up, and to make people feel less alone. Because growing up, I thought I was abnormal, weird and weak for being the way I was. I was ashamed that I “wasn’t like the rest”.
I don’t want anyone else to EVER feel that way.

But mental health is real.
And while of course I would love to keep it as positive as I possibly can, that would defeat the object of my page. If I suffer in silence without speaking up, people will do the same. If I am open, people will feel more prompted to speak up. And that is what I want to do. 

You never truly know how bad someone may be suffering deep down, and how close they could be to giving up.

So please, think before you write.
💗

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Hannah | FTMH 💗 on July 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
So today I went round London and put up lots of different quotes to try and help people as much as I possibly can. I really want to make a positive impact and if I can help even just one person, that’s enough for me and my job is done.

I’ve been in that place where I felt like I couldn’t see a way out. I don’t want anyone else to feel that way. 

Here are a few of what I put up. There was loads more 🤪

Not talking about suicide reinforces the idea that it is not ok to talk about. Which should never be the case.

I hope that today I’ve made someone feel something.
If you ever see them make sure you let me know. 💗

Your brain was focused on surviving while they were free to develop and grow. You might feel like you're behind but it's because you were doing your best to survive.'.

node.text:
Wow. Who feels me on this one?

P.S.. it is PERFECTLY OK! You were using the strength and courage everyday to get through.. and that takes real bravery.

So please give yourself the credit you deserve and don’t put yourself down, because the fact you’re still here is the biggest achievement in itself. ❤️
